      • escape

        public CSV.Format escape(char e)
        Set escape character.

        By default the separator is the double quote character ("). Note that escaping follows the RFC-4180 convention, except for the possibility of having line breaks and carriage returns within escaped sequences.

        Parameters:
        e - Character to use as escape character.
        Returns:
        The object instance (to facilitate chained calls).

      • lineComment

        @Deprecated
public CSV.Format lineComment(String lcs)
        Deprecated. As of release 1.4, replaced by lineComment(char).
        Set line comment character. Lines starting with the specified character will be ignored. By default no comment character is set.
        Parameters:
        lcs - Line comment sequence (should contain one character, call has been deprecated).
        Returns:
        The object instance (to facilitate chained calls).

      • alwaysEscapeOutput

        public CSV.Format alwaysEscapeOutput()
        Indicates that the escape sequence should always be used when writing values. If not set (the default) escape sequences will be written only when necessary.

        The object instance (to facilitate chained calls).
